      "type": "heading",
      "content": "🧠 1️⃣ SUBJECT PRONOUNS (કર્તા)"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "👉 Sentence માં action કરનાર."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "content": [
        "I play.",
        "She is smart.",
        "They are here."
      ]
    },
    {
        "type": "note",
        "content": "💡 **Why?**<br/>કર્તા એટલે work કોણ કરે છે."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": "🎯 2️⃣ OBJECT PRONOUNS (કર્મ)"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "👉 Action જેને મળે છે / Preposition પછી આવે છે."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "content": [
        "He called me.",
        "I will help them.",
        "Give it to her."
      ]
    },
    {
        "type": "note",
        "content": "💡 **Why?**<br/>Verb પછી હંમેશા object આવે."
    },
     {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": "🏠 3️⃣ POSSESSIVE ADJECTIVES"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "👉 પછી noun આવે."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "content": [
        "This is my book.",
        "That is their car."
      ]
    },
    {
        "type": "note",
        "content": "💡 **Why?**<br/>Ownership + Noun combo."
    },
     {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": "🔑 4️⃣ POSSESSIVE PRONOUNS (Noun નથી આવતું)"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "👉 mine, yours, his, hers, ours, theirs"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "content": [
        "This book is mine.",
        "The house is theirs."
      ]
    },
    {
        "type": "note",
        "content": "💡 **Why?**<br/>Ownership alone."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": "🪞 5️⃣ REFLEXIVE PRONOUNS"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "👉 Action પોતાના ઉપર → myself, yourself, himself…"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "content": [
        "I hurt myself.",
        "They enjoyed themselves."
      ]
    },
    {
        "type": "note",
        "content": "💡 **Why?**<br/>Doer & receiver same."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": "🫱🏼‍🫲🏻 6️⃣ RECIPROCAL PRONOUNS"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "👉 બે લોકો → each other<br/>👉 ઘણા → one another"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "content": [
        "Twins love each other.",
        "Students help one another."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": "⚖️ 7️⃣ 231 RULE (Order of Pronouns)"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "👉 Positive sentence → You → He/She → I"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "content": [
        "✔ **Correct:** You, he and I will go.",
        "❌ **Wrong:** I, you and he will go."
      ]
    },
    {
        "type": "note",
        "content": "💡 **Why?**<br/>Respect order → 2 → 3 → 1"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": "🪫 8️⃣ Preposition પછી Object Case"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "👉 between, to, for, with… પછી → me, him, her, us, them"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "content": [
        "✔ **Examples:**",
        "between you and me",
        "with him",
        "for them",
        "❌ **Wrong:** between you and I"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": "🌧 9️⃣ “IT” નો સાચો ઉપયોગ"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "👉 Weather, time, distance, animal, thing"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "content": [
        "It is raining.",
        "It is 4 PM.",
        "I have a cat. It is cute."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": "🏁 🔟 Comparison Rule (than/as)"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "👉 Formal → Subject Case<br/>👉 Informal → Object Case"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "content": [
        "✔ **Formal:** He is taller than I (am).",
        "✔ **Spoken:** He is taller than me."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": "📝 1️⃣1️⃣ Pronoun + Noun Rule"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "👉 Pronoun હંમેશા noun પહેલાં"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "content": [
        "✔ **Examples:**",
        "We students will speak.",
        "You boys come here.",
        "❌ **Wrong:** Students we will speak."
      ]
    },
